data.title: U.S. Navy Rear Admiral Kenneth Whitesell, right, the commander of Carrier Strike Group (CSG) 4, speaks to Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 162 (REIN), 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit
data.meta_description: Download this stock image: U.S. Navy Rear Admiral Kenneth Whitesell, right, the commander of Carrier Strike Group (CSG) 4, speaks to Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 162 (REIN), 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), during a visit aboard the amphibious transport dock ship USS New York (LPD 21), Nov. 15, 2017. Whitesell visited the USS New York during Combined Composite Unit Training Exercise (COMPTUEX), the capstone event for the Iwo Jima Amphibious Readiness Group (ARG)/MEU team prior to deployment, to learn the capabilities of the Air Combat Element aboard the ship. U.S. Navy Rear Admiral Kenneth Whitesell, right, the commander of Carrier Strike Group (CSG) 4, speaks to Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 162 (REIN), 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), during a visit aboard the amphibious transport dock ship USS New York (LPD 21), Nov. 15, 2017. Whitesell visited the USS New York during Combined Composite Unit Training Exercise (COMPTUEX), the capstone event for the Iwo Jima Amphibious Readiness Group (ARG)/MEU team prior to deployment, to learn the capabilities of the Air Combat Element aboard the ship.
